A 37-year-old yam seller, Mrs Amina Gambo, has, slumped and died inside the Abaji Area Council Central Market in the FCT. A witness, Garba Saidu, said that the incident occured on Tuesday around 2pm while the victim was attending to a customer. He said she fell to the ground and was rushed to the hospital where she was confirmed dead. A family member of the deceased, simply identified as Salihu, said the woman, a mother of three, was hale and hearty that fateful day when she left home for the market, adding that her remains have been buried according to Islamic rites. 